article.headline: Barlow, Illinois-Chicago bury Wagner 94-76
article.story: ESTERO, Fla. -- Kelsey Barlow sparked a second half run and finished with a career-high 38 points on Wednesday night to lead Illinois-Chicago to a 94-76 victory over Wagner for third place in the Gulf Coast Showcase. Barlow's point total set a tournament high and tied for third most in UIC's program history. He had just set a career high with 17 against San Diego two nights ago in the opening round. UIC (3-4) led Wagner 55-45 with 15:18 left. Barlow scored 21 points over the next 10 minutes as the Flames extended their lead to 90-59. Barlow also had seven rebounds, five assists and five 3-pointers. Wagner (4-4) had five technical fouls, including two for head coach Bashir Mason who was ejected with 6:17 remaining. The Seahawks' leading scorer, Latif Rivers, got a technical in the second half while sitting on the bench -- it was also his fourth foul.
